= TTF_RenderGlyph_Blended =

Create a 32-bit ARGB surface and render the given glyph at high quality, using alpha blending to dither the font with the given color.

== Syntax ==

<syntaxhighlight lang='c'>
SDL_Surface * TTF_RenderGlyph_Blended(TTF_Font *font,
Uint16 ch, SDL_Color fg);
</syntaxhighlight>

== Function Parameters ==

{|
|'''font'''
|[[TTF_Font]] handle
|-
|'''ch'''
|character index
|-
|'''fg'''
|foreground color
|}

== Return Value ==

Returns the new surface, or NULL if there was an error.

== Remarks ==

The glyph is rendered without any padding or centering in the X direction,
and aligned normally in the Y direction. This function returns the new
surface, or NULL if there was an error.

